(82, 1, '2011-12-08 17:09:06', '2011-12-08 17:09:06', '<p>Tenerife is blessed with an amazing variety of activities ensuring there is something to suit every holidaymaker regardless of age or taste. The most popular excursions and activities are shown in this section, many with a direct link to their own website. The Island is awash with excursion agencies so it is posible to book directly with the host operator on line or thru an agency located close to your holiday destination. You can obtain special deals from some attraction operators. For example Loro Park and Siam Park offer a discounted double ticket as do Aqualand and Jungle Park. Most attractions also offer free transportation from selected locations within the Resort areas.</p>\r\n<p> [locations category="17" addresses=”true” type="map" sort_by="title"]</p>', 'Excursions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'excursions', '', '', '2012-09-23 15:30:45', '2012-09-23 15:30:45', '', 2, 'http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/?page_id=82', 3, 'page', '', 0),
(529, 1, '2012-09-23 15:32:38', '2012-09-23 15:32:38', '<p> <a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/freebird-1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-518" title="freebird-1" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/freebird-1-300x205.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="205" /></a>If you love dolphins and whales, then there are several boat excursions that leave from the Marina at Puerto Colon in Playa de las Americas and from the Port in Los Cristianos, including catamarans, pirate boats and glass bottom boats.   The Freebird sailing out of Puerto Colon are two of the more popular trips. Sail into the open waters and watch as the dolphins play alongside the boats, and keep your eyes open for the whales. A must for all dolphin and whales fans!</p>', 'Freebird', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '517-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-23 15:32:38', '2012-09-23 15:32:38', '', 517, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/517-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(530, 1, '2012-09-23 15:36:45', '2012-09-23 15:36:45', '<p><a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/mount-teide-national-park-1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-532" title="mount-teide-national-park-1" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/mount-teide-national-park-1-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a>Situated on the island of Tenerife, Teide National Park features the Teide-Pico Viejo strato volcano that, at 3,718 m, is the highest peak on Spanish soil. Rising 7,500 m above the ocean floor, it is regarded as the world’s third-tallest volcanic structure and stands in a spectacular environment.</p>\r\n<p>The visual impact of the site is all the greater due to atmospheric conditions that create constantly changing textures and tones in the landscape and a ‘sea of clouds’ that forms a visually impressive backdrop to the mountain. The journey takes you through the highest village in Spain, Vilaflor, Canarian pine forests and lunar landscapes. The summit of Mount Teide is only accessible by cable car from the visitor centre, where you will also find a café bar and gift shop.  Full day or half-day trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.</p>', 'Mount Teide National Park', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mount-teide-national-park', '', '', '2012-09-23 15:37:16', '2012-09-23 15:37:16', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=530', 0, 'location', '', 0),
