(196, 1, '2011-12-08 06:04:56', '2011-12-08 06:04:56', 'Tenerife, known as the Island of Eternal Spring is located in the Atlantic, just off the north coast of Africa and enjoys a pleasant temperature in both the summer and winter; making it an excellent choice for a holiday at any time of the year. The coastal areas of Tenerife receive the best weather, with the south and the west enjoying the most sunshine, averaging up to 11 hours a day in the summer months.\r\n\r\nThe temperatures throughout the year vary very little on Tenerife ranging from 15c in the winter up to 24c in the summer. Even on its hottest days, the temperature on Tenerife rarely gets higher than 30c.  The north-easterly trade winds ensure the temperatures on Tenerife stay constant, and add some welcome breezes, which tend to be stronger during the winter. Tenerife does not have a rainy season, but the island does see an occasional shower between November and March.\r\n\r\nDivided by a mountain range, the weather on Tenerife does vary depending on location on the island. The south offers a dry climate, and tends to be hotter and sunnier than the north, making it a much more popular tourist destination. North Tenerife has a slightly wetter climate, and is home to a much greener landscape.  The volcano El Teide in the centre of the island, boasting a peak of almost 4000m, can be seen from many beaches and frequently remains snow-capped during the winter months.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19" title="Average Temperatures" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/average-temperatures.jpg" alt="Average Temperatures" width="500" height="239" />\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20" title="Average Rainfall" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/average-rainfall.jpg" alt="Average Rainfall" width="500" height="239" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Check out the weather for your proposed holiday a few days before your departure.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aemet.es/en/eltiempo/prediccion/localidades/adeje-38010" target="_blank">http://www.aemet.es/en/eltiempo/prediccion/localidades/adeje-38010</a>', 'Weather', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '17-revision-3', '', '', '2011-12-08 06:04:56', '2011-12-08 06:04:56', '', 17, 'http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/17-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(197, 1, '2011-12-08 17:41:59', '2011-12-08 17:41:59', 'Tenerife is blessed with an amazing variety of activities ensuring there is something to suit every holidaymaker regardless of age or taste. The most popular excursions and activities are shown in this section, many with a direct link to their own website. The Island is awash with excursion agencies so it is posible to book directly with the host operator on line or thru an agency located close to your holiday destination. You can obtain special deals from some attraction operators.  For example Loro Park and Siam Park offer a discounted double ticket as do Aqualand and Jungle Park.  Most attractions also offer free  transportation from selected locations within the Resort areas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="10">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-86" title="Monkey Park" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/monkey-park.jpg" alt="Monkey Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Monkey Park</h3>\r\nMonkey Park is located just off the TF-1 approximately 5 minutes from Los Cristianos. Although not as big as Loro Parque and Jungle Park, the Monkey Park is a favourite with visitors. You won''t find fancy gift shops and restaurants here, and all the money made from entrance fees and the sale of monkey food is put back into the Park. If you love animals, particularly monkeys, then the Monkey Park is definitely worthy of a visit.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.monkeypark.com" target="_blank">www.monkeypark.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://easyinfomatics.com/projects/tenerife/upload/guidetotenerife/dolphin-excursions.jpg" alt="Dolphins and Whales" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Dolphins and Whales</h3>\r\nIf you love dolphins and whales, then there are several boat excursions that leave from the Marina at Puerto Colon in Playa de las Americas  and from the Port at Los Cristianos, including catamarans, pirate boats and glass bottom boats. Sail into the open waters and watch as the dolphins play alongside the boats, and keep your eyes open for the whales. <strong>A must for all dolphin and whales fans!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.freebirdone.com" target="_blank">www.freebirdone.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-95" title="Tenerife Pearl" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/tenerife-pearl.jpg" alt="Tenerife Pearl" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Tenerife Pearl</h3>\r\nIf you love pearls or are celebrating a special occasion, why not visit Tenerife Pearl. Part of the World Pearl Group and situated in Armeñime, only 15 minutes drive from Los Cristianos, Tenerife Pearl has over 1,500m2 of Pearls and Pearl Jewellery, all beautifully displayed. Before you leave you can enjoy a meal in the café and have your picture taken at the Fountain of Love. A free coach service operates from Los Cristianos, Las Americas, Costa Adeje and Golf del Sur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.tenerifepearl.com/index.html" target="_blank">www.tenerifepearl.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-97" title="Guimar Pyramids" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/guimar-pyramids.jpg" alt="Guimar Pyramids" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Guimar Pyramids</h3>\r\nIf history interests you then visit The Guimar Pyramids Ethnographic Park which is located inland from Tenerife''s east coast. These six pyramids are similar to those in Sicily, Mexico, Mesopotamia, Polinesia and Peru and have been extensively researched since the early 1990’s by Norwegian anthropologist, Thor Heyerdahl. The site has an information centre, café, shop and childrens playground. Buses are available from various pick up points in the South of Tenerife.  Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.piramidesdeguimar.net/" target="_blank">www.piramidesdeguimar.net</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-98" title="Mount Teide Naitonal Park" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/teide-national-park.jpg" alt="Mount Teide Naitonal Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Mount Teide/Las Cañadas National Park</h3>\r\nMount Teide is the heart of Tenerife and one of the most visited attractions on the island. The journey takes you through the highest village in Spain, Vilaflor, Canarian pine forests and lunar landscapes. The summit of Mount Teide is only accessible by cable car from the visitor centre, where you will also find a café bar and gift shop.  Full day or half day trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-99" title="Siam Park" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/siam-park.jpg" alt="Siam Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Siam Park</h3>\r\nSiam Park provides a perfect day out for families, groups of friends and conference and incentive teams.Inspired by the old King of Thailand, Siam, the water park is the largest in Europe with more than a 52 million euro investment and 185,000 square metres of thrilling attractions along with 25 ‘Thai’ style buildings. As well as all the exhilarating attractions there are numerous restaurants, bars, cocktail bars, chillout areas and even a Thai floating market!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.siampark.net/en/" target="_blank">www.siampark.net</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-100" title="Loro Parque" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/loroparque.jpg" alt="Loro Parque" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Loro Parque</h3>\r\nLoro Parque has always been known as one of the top visitor attractions on Tenerife, and with around 1.5 million visitors each year, it''s easy to see why.Originally it was mainly a Parrot park, however the site now covers a massive 135,000 square metres and Loro Parque is home to some of the worlds most fascinating and exotic animals including Dolphins, Orca whales, Tigers, Penguins and sea-lions. It''s a great day out for everyone.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.loroparque.com/en/" target="_blank">www.loroparque.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-101" title="Jungle Park" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/jungle-park.jpg" alt="Jungle Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Jungle Park</h3>\r\nJungle Park (Las Aguilas Parque) is a spectacular zoological and botanical park in the mountains of Aguilas del Teide and yet less than 10 minutes away from Los Cristianos. Jungle Park provides approximately 75,000m2 of natural habitat in which over 500 animals live including, chimps, gibbons and big cats. Don’t miss the bird shows where you can experience birds of prey and colourful exotic birds in free flight displaying their skills.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aguilasjunglepark.com" target="_blank">www.aguilasjunglepark.com </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-102" title="Medieval Castle" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/medieval-castle.jpg" alt="Medieval Castle" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Medieval Castle</h3>\r\nFrom the moment you enter the grounds, you find yourself in an authentic medieval world. In theTournament Hall, the show of medieval fights and games will take place in the presence of the Counts in their Royal  Box seats. The Medieval adventure is an exciting and enjoyable attraction suitable for the whole family. It''s an experience that shouldn''t be missed! During the Tournament, you will be served the banquet just as it was done in medieval times; The soup is drunk and an entire chicken per person with its garnish  is eaten by hand. The dinner is completed with dessert and beverages.  Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.castillosanmiguel.com/castilloinformacion-en.html" target="_blank">www.castillosanmiguel.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-104" title="Yellow Submarine" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/yellow-submarine.jpg" alt="Yellow Submarine" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Yellow Submarine</h3>\r\nExperience a dive on board a real submarine which will take you below the waters of San Miguel Marina.You will experience the true underwater world of Tenerife. We offer a free daily bus service when you book your dive from the main resort areas of Tenerife (Playa de las Americas/ Los Cristianos/ Los Gigantes etc.).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.submarinesafaris.com/" target="_blank">www.submarinesafaris.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-105" title="Aqualand" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/aqualand.jpg" alt="Aqualand" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Aqualand</h3>\r\nAqualand is situated at San Eugenio (Alto) in the Costa Adeje region, and is the only water park in the South of Tenerife with a Dolphinarium.Its internationally awarded Dolphin Shows make this a complete leisure option guaranteeing the best in entertainment and enjoyment.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aqualand.es/tenerife/index.php" target="_blank">www.aqualand.es</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/quad-park.jpg" alt="Quad Bikes" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Quad Bikes</h3>\r\nExperience the thrill and challenge of negotiating cross country trails and circuits, whilst enjoying some of the best views in the south of Tenerife. There are 200,000 sq metres of trail riding routes and circuits for you to explore! Located just ten minutes from Los Cristianos / Las Americas. Free local collection from resorts available. Open from 9.30 a.m. until dusk, 7 days per week.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.quadparktenerife.com/" target="_blank">www.quadparktenerife.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/karting.jpg" alt="Karting" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Karting</h3>\r\nWelcome to the Karting Club Tenerife 1200 meters of fun and even 270cc. Of pure adrenaline! Come and experience the feelings of a professional behind the wheel! <strong>2 circuits:</strong> 1 senior and 1 junior to ensure maximum enjoyment for the whole family. The best facilities equipped with maximum security. Free bus service available.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.kartingtenerife.com/" target="_blank">www.kartingtenerife.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/la-gomera.jpg" alt="La gomera" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Island Tours &amp; Gomera</h3>\r\nThere are a wide variety of island tours in Tenerife taking in all the major natural attractions and locations. You may also like to book a full-day all- inclusive tour of the neighbouring island La Gomera. Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/bob-diving.jpg" alt="Bob Diving" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Bob Diving</h3>\r\nFirst there was scuba diving... <strong>and then there was BOB Diving!</strong> All the underwater fun of traditional scuba diving, with much less effort. Despite looking like something secret agent 007 might use, you don''t need to be James Bond to enjoy exploring Tenerife''s underwater world. Our modern underwater scooters can be used by anyone. They are safe, easy and exciting. Safari BOB in Tenerife is the first BOB diving centre in Europe, operating since 1997, so while on holiday on the island, don’t miss the opportunity to enjoy a fabulous underwater experience that will be the highlight of your trip. You’ll find Safari BOB Diving in Puerto Colon, Playa de Las Americas, Pier no. 4.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.bob-diving.com/" target="_blank">www.bob-diving.com  </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/camel-park.jpg" alt="Camel Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Camel Park</h3>\r\nJust 10 minutes away from Los Cristianos and Playa de las Américas, in rural surroundings, you can have a nice time riding a camel, seeing the farm animals (goats, donkeys,ducks,hens,chicks,grey parrots or dogs) and enjoy an apertive drink at the typical canarian house of the place. In the farm there is a souvenir shop where you can purchase different presents and camel figures. There is free transport to the farm from the south of the island.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.camelpark.es/en/index.html" target="_blank">www.camelpark.es</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Excursions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-15', '', '', '2011-12-08 17:41:59', '2011-12-08 17:41:59', '', 82, 'http://web-dropbox.com/clients/tenerife/82-revision-15/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
