(325, 1, '2012-09-20 00:16:19', '2012-09-20 00:16:19', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-buenavista-pic.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-376" title="golf-buenavista-pic" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-buenavista-pic-300x196.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a>Buenavista Golf is located in the north-western corner of the island of Tenerife, in the region of Daute Isla Baja.  The golf course was designed by Severiano Ballesteros and opened in 2004.\n\nThe 18 hole, par 72 course, has a length of 6,019 metres and has 6 holes each of par 3, par 4 and par 5.\n\nThe outstanding holes are closer to the coast and the player seems to hit the ball right into the ocean or into the lake of holes 9 and 18 that are connected by a waterfall', 'Buena Vista Golf', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '320-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-20 00:16:19', '2012-09-20 00:16:19', '', 320, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/320-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(327, 1, '2012-09-08 11:32:58', '2012-09-08 11:32:58', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-del-sur-pic.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-377" title="golf-del-sur-pic" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-del-sur-pic-300x190.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="190" /></a>The original project of 27 holes was designed by the Spanish course architect Pepe Gancedo.  But Manuel Piñero was the person charged in 2005 of turning Golf del Sur into the only golf course in the Canary Islands with 3 loops each offering 9 holes of par 36.\r\n\r\nThe 27 holes are perfectly divided on the three courses: the North course of 2,949 metres, the South course of 2,957 metre, and the Links course of 2,853 metres each offer 2 par 3’s, 2 par 5’s and 5 par 4’s. The topology of the area has a remarkable influence on the features of each round. The presence of the sea and the impressive ravines on the course, give the player the opportunity to enjoy each visit made to Golf del Sur.\r\n\r\nThe fairways, wide and undulating, are dotted with many natural obstacles. The presence of various water hazards is in clear contrast with the incredible volcanic sand bunkers protecting the greens.', 'Golf del Sur', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'golf-del-sur', '', '', '2012-09-20 00:42:08', '2012-09-20 00:42:08', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=327', 0, 'location', '', 0),
(328, 1, '2012-09-20 00:39:24', '2012-09-20 00:39:24', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-del-sur-pic.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-377" title="golf-del-sur-pic" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/golf-del-sur-pic-300x190.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="190" /></a>The original project of 27 holes was designed by the Spanish course architect Pepe Gancedo.  But Manuel Piñero was the person charged in 2005 of turning Golf del Sur into the only golf course in the Canary Islands with 3 loops each offering 9 holes of par 36.\n\nThe 27 holes are perfectly divided on the three courses: the North course of 2,949 metres, the South course of 2,957 metre, and the Links course of 2,853 metres each offer 2 par 3’s, 2 par 5’s and 5 par 4’s. The topology of the area has a remarkable influence on the features of each round. The presence of the sea and the impressive ravines on the course, give the player the opportunity to enjoy each visit made to Golf del Sur.\n\nThe fairways, wide and undulating, are dotted with many natural obstacles. The presence of various water hazards is in clear contrast with the incredible volcanic sand bunkers protecting the greens.', 'Golf del Sur', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '327-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-20 00:39:24', '2012-09-20 00:39:24', '', 327, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/327-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
