(405, 1, '2012-09-22 20:39:24', '2012-09-22 20:39:24', 'Playa de las Américas is a purpose-built holiday resort area. It straddles the Municipalities of Arona and Adeje. Building commenced in the 1960s beside the town of Los Cristianos and stretched northward towards the Costa Adeje and is home to nearly 100 Hotels and apartment complexes.\n\nThe resort area features bars, nightclubs, restaurants, attractions, and four beaches, most of which are man-made with imported sand from Africa due to the dark colour of the native volcanic sand. Playa de las Americas is a centre of nightlife in Tenerife. Nightlife is spread around the resorts and includes among others the Veronicas Strip, Starco Commercial Centre and the Patch.   Major attractions like the Siam Park are located within the resort area.  Playa de las Americas is home to one of the two main hospitals of the south of the Island and is also home to C.D. Marino who play in the lower divisions of the Spanish Football league.\n\nPlaya de las Americas is 19kms from Tenerife’s South Airport, a journey that takes approximately 20 minutes.', 'Playa de las Americas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '404-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-22 20:39:24', '2012-09-22 20:39:24', '', 404, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/404-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
