(436, 1, '2012-09-22 21:41:30', '2012-09-22 21:41:30', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/playa-san-juan.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-437" title="playa-san-juan" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/playa-san-juan-300x236.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="236" /></a>Playa San Juan is a typical Canarian village that has improved its tourist infrastructure without losing any of its charm.  It is located in the municipality of Guia de Isora and is some 37 kms or 40 minutes drive from the South Airport.  It is one of the few remaining working fishing villages in Tenerife and also offers whale and dolphin safaris from the small port.  The new Abama Golf resort is five minutes away and the town hosts a local market twice a week.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 beaches to found here, a small cove with shallow waters which is popular with families with small children and the other is a long sandy beach, which has recently been developed. The crystal clear waters make it a favoured diving spot. There is a promenade that runs the full length of the village, which is dotted with restaurants offering international and local cuisines, many with fresh fish specialities. A few small shops and bars can also be found here.<strong></strong>', 'Playa de San Juan', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'playa-de-san-juan', '', '', '2012-09-22 21:41:30', '2012-09-22 21:41:30', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=436', 0, 'location', '', 0),
