(441, 1, '2012-09-22 21:49:10', '2012-09-22 21:49:10', 'Playa de la Arena is the most southerly of three resort areas that also includes Puerto Santiago and Los Gigantes to make up the holiday coastline of the municipality of Santiago del Teide.\r\n\r\nThe three resorts span a distance of less than three kms and at their furthest point are 46 kms from the South Airport, a journey that can take between 45 minutes and an hour depending on the traffic.  Playa La Arena has a stunning natural beach formed of black sand, a by-product of the island''s volcanic past.  It is edged with palm trees and a broad, flower-laden promenade with a small parade of shops and a selection of typical Canarian bars, restaurants, and welcoming pavement cafes.  The resort along with neighbouring Puerto de Santiago is a growing tourist centre, offering ideal accommodation for family holidays in the sun. It''s a quieter spot than some of Tenerife''s more boisterous resorts, so would suit those seeking a relaxing holiday.\r\n\r\nSpotlessly maintained, Playa de la Arena beach has won the European Blue Flag award for cleanliness and there are water sports available in peak season. The beach is gently shelving, affording good swimming and paddling conditions and clear weather permitting, you can see across the water to the neighbouring Canary Island of  La Gomera.', 'Playa de la Arena', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'playa-de-la-arena', '', '', '2012-09-22 21:49:10', '2012-09-22 21:49:10', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=441', 0, 'location', '', 0),
