(443, 1, '2012-09-22 21:51:34', '2012-09-22 21:51:34', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/puerto-santiago.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-444" title="puerto-santiago" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/puerto-santiago-300x221.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="221" /></a>Puerto Santiago is the middle of three resort areas that also includes Play de la Arena and Los Gigantes to make up the holiday coastline of the municipality of Santiago del Teide.  The three resorts span a distance of less than three kms and at their furthest point are 46 kms from the South Airport, a journey that can take between 45 minutes and one hour depending on the traffic.  Puerto Santiago was once a small fishing village but has now given up its fishing heritage in favour of tourism.\r\n\r\nPuerto Santiago is probably the most traditional of the three results and is does boast a small beach but without the facilities of Playa de la Arena, which is just 1,000 metres to the south.', 'Puerto Santiago', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'puerto-santiago', '', '', '2012-09-22 21:51:34', '2012-09-22 21:51:34', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=443', 0, 'location', '', 0),
