(445, 1, '2012-09-22 21:53:06', '2012-09-22 21:53:06', 'Los Gigantes is the most northerly of three resort areas that also includes Playa de la Arena and Puerto Santiago to make up the holiday coastline of the municipality of Santiago del Teide.  The three resorts span a distance of less than three kms and at their furthest point are 46 kms from the South Airport, a journey that can take between 45 minutes and an hour depending on the traffic.  Los Gigantes, or ''The Cliffs of the Giants'', is located on the western coast of Tenerife and is home to a very small sandy beach and a busy yacht marina.\r\n\r\nThe town of Los Gigantes is named after, and lies at the foot of, the imposing vertical cliffs of the same name. This stunning resort is set in a rocky cove facing the Atlantic Ocean, with cliffs protruding up to 800m over the sea.  Los Gigantes is an attractive and somewhat exclusive resort, with traditional low-rise hotels and apartment buildings blending well into the town, and a good range of shops selling everything from souvenirs to designer labels. Built into the cliff face, Los Gigantes has some steep and winding narrow streets, with most of the facilities situated uphill from the seafront. The centre of Los Gigantes has a pedestrianised area based around the old church, and offers a good choice of bars, restaurants and shops.\r\n\r\nAt the foot of the cliffs lies the small beach of Los Gigantes. Made of black volcanic sand, the beach here is good for families and doesn’t get too crowded.  Next to the beach is the bustling marina of Los Gigantes, the hub of the resort. It is home to both expensive yachts and fishing boats, and is the departure point for the many popular boat trips up and down the coastline. This is the best way to experience the dramatic cliffs of Los Gigantes up close, and also a fun way to spot the colonies of dolphins and whales that swim freely in these waters.<strong></strong>', 'Los Gigantes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'los-gigantes', '', '', '2012-09-22 21:54:14', '2012-09-22 21:54:14', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=445', 0, 'location', '', 0),
