(458, 1, '2012-09-22 22:31:05', '2012-09-22 22:31:05', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/los-abrigos.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-459" title="los-abrigos" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/los-abrigos-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>Los Abrigos is a fishing village on the south coast of Tenerife in the municipality of Granadilla de Abona.   Colourful fishing boats bobbing on the waters of the charming little harbour is a far cry from the neon lights and party atmosphere of major tourist hang outs like Los Cristianos and Playa de las Americas.  This is an example of real Tenerife, a hidden gem that many holidaymakers are yet to explore.\r\n\r\nA little off-the-beaten track but only a short walk from Golf del Sur, Los Abrigos has got a lot going for it. A paradise for seafood and fish lovers, lots of lovely restaurants line the pretty harbour are the perfect place to sample local dishes. They are among the best fish restaurants in Tenerife!  And it’s not just the mix of fresh crab, lobster, oysters, mussels, seam bream etc, the restaurants serve a good mix of Canarian cuisine, prime cuts of meat, tapas and of course paella.   Wherever you’re staying, you’ll be impressed with this slice of authentic island life. Los Abrigos has its own volcanic beach, a nice little cove, a traditional Canarian plaza with a cute little church and a few cafés and shops. And Tuesday night is market night.  Sample the goods on offer at Tenerife’s only evening market, which starts at 6pm. before sampling one of the harbour restaurants or indeed several others elsewhere in the village.\r\n\r\nThe village has grown in recent years and now offers a fair selection of holiday accommodation.  If you plan to stay here, it will take less than 15 minutes to cover the 13 kms to the south airport.<em>\r\n\r\n</em><em></em>', 'Los Abrigos', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'los-abrigos', '', '', '2012-09-22 22:31:05', '2012-09-22 22:31:05', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=458', 0, 'location', '', 0),
(459, 1, '2012-09-22 22:30:47', '2012-09-22 22:30:47', '', 'los-abrigos', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'los-abrigos', '', '', '2012-09-22 22:30:47', '2012-09-22 22:30:47', '', 458, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/los-abrigos.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(460, 1, '2012-09-22 22:33:23', '2012-09-22 22:33:23', 'El Médano has long been popular with island residents, because of its natural sandy beaches and year round sunny climate. It is between two mountains, which form cliffs into the sea.  Both Montaña Pelada<strong>, ‘</strong>the bald mountain’, and ‘the red mountain, Montaña Roja, are Nature Reserve areas and can be climbed in less than half an hour giving extensive views.  Playa El Médano is claimed to be the longest natural sandy beach in Tenerife. It stretches from Plaza de El Médano, the town square, to the foot of Montaña Roja to the west. There are wide variety of restaurants and bars around the square and along the boardwalk at the top of the beach. This whole area is traffic free.  By the square, the beach is sheltered from the predominantly easterly wind by the Hotel El Medano, which extends out over the sea.\r\n\r\nTo the east of the Hotel Medano is El Meulle, the small harbour.  There are a good variety of small shops in El Médano including small supermarkets, a pharmacy, opticians, photographers, and of course many small boutiques, souvenir and gift shops. In the town square are the Tourist Information Office and two Banks and the taxi stand. The town has many good restaurants, including Italian, Chinese and Japanese.  El Medano is 9kms from the south airport, a journey that takes less than 15 minutes', 'El Médano', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'el-medano', '', '', '2012-09-22 22:33:23', '2012-09-22 22:33:23', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=460', 0, 'location', '', 0),
(461, 1, '2012-09-22 22:35:36', '2012-09-22 22:35:36', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/candelaria.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-462" title="candelaria" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/candelaria-300x236.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="236" /></a>Candelaria is situated on the sunny southern coast of Tenerife and is 15 kms from the capital of the island, Santa Cruz de Tenerife.   Candelaria has a population of around 25,000 people. The town has expanded significantly over the last few years but you wont find any artificially built tourism centers here.  Spending your holiday in Candelaria means enjoying the real Canarian life. The town just about offers everything you will need - shopping facilities, bars and restaurants and it has a good infrastructure.\r\n\r\nThe town has a fishing harbour and a beautiful promenade where you can go for a walk along the seafront and view the statues of the Guanche kings who once ruled the island.  At the end of the promenade is the Basilica, which houses the Black Madonna.\r\n\r\nIn particular, the renowned Italian sculptor Antonio Canova’s El Triunfo de la Candelaria (Triumph of the Virgin of Candelaria) creates much interest in its central location overseeing the town’s main plaza. Candelaria is the most important pilgrimage town in the entire Canary Islands and on the 14th and 15th of August, thousands of people from all over the Canaries will flock to see the Virgin of Candelaria, the patron saint of the archipelago.  Candelaria is 46 kms from Tenerife’s South Airport and involves a journey of about 35minutes. Alternatively, the North airport is only 23 kms distant and the journey to Candelaria takes a little over 20 mins<em></em>', 'Candelaria ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'candelaria', '', '', '2012-09-22 22:35:36', '2012-09-22 22:35:36', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=461', 0, 'location', '', 0),
