(465, 1, '2012-09-22 22:40:11', '2012-09-22 22:40:11', '<a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/puerto-de-la-cruz.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-466" title="puerto-de-la-cruz" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/puerto-de-la-cruz-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>The historic town of Puerto de la Cruz was the birthplace of tourism in Tenerife in the 17<sup>th</sup> century.  It was not until the mid twentieth century, however, that tourism really took off but despite the last forty years of mass tourism, Puerto de la Cruz, in contrast with the modern resorts of the south, has managed to maintain a strong sense of its Canarian heritage The accommodation offered in Puerto de la Cruz is also different from most of the other places on the island since hotels predominate over apartments.  The lushness of the gardens and the agreeable atmosphere are very special features of this city, which has lively places to stroll around.  Much of the area around the old fishing port is full of narrow cobbled streets lined with traditional colonial-style cafés and bars where the local people still go about their daily lives, working, eating and drinking in much the same way as they have for centuries.  The city also houses a number of buildings of great historical and artistic value.  Its old world charm lives side by side with a wide range of quality hotels and apartment complexes that ensure a perfect place to stay for all tastes and budgets. In addition, there is a selection of high-end boutiques, charming plazas and a wealth of tourist attractions, including the renowned Casino Tauro, which are located all over the resort.   The beaches of Puerto are of black sand and not the most attractive but to compensate the local council commissioned Canarian architect and artist César Manrique, to create the fabulous 8 acre Lido Martinez, a water park consisting of several swimming pools and a salt water lake surrounded by sub-tropical gardens right on the seafront in the centre of Puerto.\r\n\r\nPuerto de la Cruz is located on the north coast of Tenerife and as such is closer to the north airport being only 28 kms and 25 minutes distant.  Conversely the south airport where most tourist flights land is 93 kms distant and involves a journey of over an hour.<em></em>', 'Puerto de la Cruz', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'puerto-de-la-cruz', '', '', '2012-09-22 22:40:11', '2012-09-22 22:40:11', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=465', 0, 'location', '', 0),
