ach''s southern side, blocks out the vista of Las Americas beyond.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Other Notable Beaches in Tenerife</h2>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="10">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/beach-puertito.jpg" alt="El Puertito" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3><a name="b8"></a>El Puertito</h3>\r\n<p>Nestling between the resorts on the south and southwest coasts, the bay at El Puertito is probably what Tenerife''s southern fishing hamlets looked like before the property developers moved in. Whitewashed buildings, a fish restaurant, aquamarine water, brightly coloured fishing boats and pale gold sand make you feel as though you''re on an island that hasn''t been discovered yet.</p>\r\n<p><strong>But where is it?</strong> A small sign points the way from the TF47 just outside Armeñime on the road west to Los Gigantes.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/beach-de-la-arena.jpg" alt="Playa de la Arena" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3><a name="b9"></a>Playa de la Arena</h3>\r\n<p>''Playa de la Arenas'' simply means ''sandy beach''. The best one is found at the resort of the same name. A small, blue flag beach which is set in one of the nicest coves on Tenerife. With the most sunshine hours on the island, great views to the island of La Gomera and stunning sunsets, this is a sun worshipper''s dream.</p>\r\n<p><strong>But where is it?</strong> On Tenerife''s sunny west coast, near <a href="http://www.realtenerifeislanddrives.com/Los%20Gigantes.html" target="_blank">Los Gigantes</a>, in the centre of the small resort of <a href="http://www.realtenerifeislanddrives.com/Apartment.html" target="_blank">Playa de la Arena</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/beach-medano.jpg" alt="El MÃ©dano" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3><a name="b10"></a>El Médano</h3>\r\n<p>A rarity for a beach on Tenerife, a golden(ish) beach which isn''t man made. One of the longest beaches on Tenerife, book ended on one side by El Médano and Montaña Roja on the other. A bleached wooden boardwalk runs almost the length of the beach passing surreal pumice rock formations and scores of rainbow bright windsurfers and kite-boarders. The presence of these ''surf dudes'' should warn you that the wind is a constant companion here. It might make pretty patterns in the sand, but it isn''t always ideal for sunbathing. One of the most interesting beaches on Tenerife.</p>\r\n<p><strong>But where is it?</strong> Right beside the town of the same name just past the airport on the way to Santa Cruz.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/beach-la-tejita.jpg" alt="Playa de la Tejita" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3><a name="b11"></a>Playa de la Tejita</h3>\r\n<p>Another pale golden beach so long and wide you could land a jumbo jet on it, which isn''t beyond the realms of possibility considering it''s right next to the airport. It''s another windy beach which makes it the ideal location for Granadilla''s annual kite festival in September. The Montaña Roja end of the beach is popular with nudists.</p>\r\n<p><strong>But where is it? </strong>Beyond El Médano, on the other side of Montaña Roja.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/beach-las-teresitas.jpg" alt="Playa de las Teresitas" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3><a name="b12"></a>Playa de las Teresitas</h3>\r\n<p>The jewel in the crown of Tenerife''s beaches and without doubt the most spectacular. It''s many people''s idea of what a tropical beach should look like. A crescent shaped, lagoon-like bay with golden sand lapped by aquamarine waters. Add palm trees and a dramatic mountain backdrop and you''ve got a perfect setting. There are changing rooms, toilets, bar restaurants and a large car park discreetly hidden behind the line of palms at the back of the beach. The man made reef makes the enclosed calm water ideal for families with young children. The only downside is that, being the east coast, it can be a tad breezy sometimes. Okay it''s a man made beach, but it looks great.</p>\r\n<p><strong>But where is it? </strong>Approx 8 kilometres beyond Santa Cruz.</p>\r\n<p><a href="#top"><strong>Back to Top</strong></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>YouTube Videos</h2>\r\n<p>There are two great videos of Tenerife''s beaches on YouTube. Each lasts about 4 minutes and gives a great insight into what''s on offer.</p>\r\n<table style="width: 650px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center" valign="middle" width="50%"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U4seYCMS3GM"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-361" title="video-thumb01" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/video-thumb01.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="152" /> </a></td>\r\n<td align="center" valign="middle" width="50%"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kYpE_IjI8xY&amp;NR=1"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-363" title="video-thumb02" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/video-thumb02.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="152" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Tenerife Beaches', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '221-revision-22', '', '', '2012-09-23 00:47:41', '2012-09-23 00:47:41', '', 221, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/221-revision-22/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(512, 1, '2012-03-27 14:17:36', '2012-03-27 14:17:36', '<iframe src="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&amp;msa=0&amp;msid=205255983672030508133.0004b8d6b3fdda05f011a&amp;t=m&amp;ll=28.278987,-16.570129&amp;spn=0.604693,0.918732&amp;z=10&amp;output=embed" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no" width="670" height="500"></iframe>\r\n\r\nTenerife is blessed with an amazing variety of activities ensuring there is something to suit every holidaymaker regardless of age or taste. The most popular excursions and activities are shown in this section, many with a direct link to their own website. The Island is awash with excursion agencies so it is posible to book directly with the host operator on line or thru an agency located close to your holiday destination. You can obtain special deals from some attraction operators.  For example Loro Park and Siam Park offer a discounted double ticket as do Aqualand and Jungle Park.  Most attractions also offer free  transportation from selected locations within the Resort areas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="10">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-86" title="Monkey Park" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/monkey-park.jpg" alt="Monkey Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Monkey Park</h3>\r\nMonkey Park is located just off the TF-1 approximately 5 minutes from Los Cristianos. Although not as big as Loro Parque and Jungle Park, the Monkey Park is a favourite with visitors. You won''t find fancy gift shops and restaurants here, and all the money made from entrance fees and the sale of monkey food is put back into the Park. If you love animals, particularly monkeys, then the Monkey Park is definitely worthy of a visit.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.monkeypark.com" target="_blank">www.monkeypark.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://easyinfomatics.com/projects/tenerife/upload/guidetotenerife/dolphin-excursions.jpg" alt="Dolphins and Whales" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Dolphins and Whales</h3>\r\nIf you love dolphins and whales, then there are several boat excursions that leave from the Marina at Puerto Colon in Playa de las Americas  and from the Port at Los Cristianos, including catamarans, pirate boats and glass bottom boats. Sail into the open waters and watch as the dolphins play alongside the boats, and keep your eyes open for the whales. <strong>A must for all dolphin and whales fans!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.freebirdone.com" target="_blank">www.freebirdone.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-95" title="Tenerife Pearl" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/tenerife-pearl.jpg" alt="Tenerife Pearl" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Tenerife Pearl</h3>\r\nIf you love pearls or are celebrating a special occasion, why not visit Tenerife Pearl. Part of the World Pearl Group and situated in Armeñime, only 15 minutes drive from Los Cristianos, Tenerife Pearl has over 1,500m2 of Pearls and Pearl Jewellery, all beautifully displayed. Before you leave you can enjoy a meal in the café and have your picture taken at the Fountain of Love. A free coach service operates from Los Cristianos, Las Americas, Costa Adeje and Golf del Sur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.tenerifepearl.com/index.html" target="_blank">www.tenerifepearl.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-97" title="Guimar Pyramids" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/guimar-pyramids.jpg" alt="Guimar Pyramids" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Guimar Pyramids</h3>\r\nIf history interests you then visit The Guimar Pyramids Ethnographic Park which is located inland from Tenerife''s east coast. These six pyramids are similar to those in Sicily, Mexico, Mesopotamia, Polinesia and Peru and have been extensively researched since the early 1990''s by Norwegian anthropologist, Thor Heyerdahl. The site has an information centre, café, shop and childrens playground. Buses are available from various pick up points in the South of Tenerife.  Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.piramidesdeguimar.net/" target="_blank">www.piramidesdeguimar.net</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-98" title="Mount Teide Naitonal Park" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/teide-national-park.jpg" alt="Mount Teide Naitonal Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Mount Teide/Las Cañadas National Park</h3>\r\nMount Teide is the heart of Tenerife and one of the most visited attractions on the island. The journey takes you through the highest village in Spain, Vilaflor, Canarian pine forests and lunar landscapes. The summit of Mount Teide is only accessible by cable car from the visitor centre, where you will also find a café bar and gift shop.  Full day or half day trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-99" title="Siam Park" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/siam-park.jpg" alt="Siam Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Siam Park</h3>\r\nSiam Park provides a perfect day out for families, groups of friends and conference and incentive teams.Inspired by the old King of Thailand, Siam, the water park is the largest in Europe with more than a 52 million euro investment and 185,000 square metres of thrilling attractions along with 25 ''Thai'' style buildings. As well as all the exhilarating attractions there are numerous restaurants, bars, cocktail bars, chillout areas and even a Thai floating market!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.siampark.net/en/" target="_blank">www.siampark.net</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-100" title="Loro Parque" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/loroparque.jpg" alt="Loro Parque" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Loro Parque</h3>\r\nLoro Parque has always been known as one of the top visitor attractions on Tenerife, and with around 1.5 million visitors each year, it''s easy to see why.Originally it was mainly a Parrot park, however the site now covers a massive 135,000 square metres and Loro Parque is home to some of the worlds most fascinating and exotic animals including Dolphins, Orca whales, Tigers, Penguins and sea-lions. It''s a great day out for everyone.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.loroparque.com/en/" target="_blank">www.loroparque.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-101" title="Jungle Park" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/jungle-park.jpg" alt="Jungle Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Jungle Park</h3>\r\nJungle Park (Las Aguilas Parque) is a spectacular zoological and botanical park in the mountains of Aguilas del Teide and yet less than 10 minutes away from Los Cristianos. Jungle Park provides approximately 75,000m2 of natural habitat in which over 500 animals live including, chimps, gibbons and big cats. Don''t miss the bird shows where you can experience birds of prey and colourful exotic birds in free flight displaying their skills.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aguilasjunglepark.com" target="_blank">www.aguilasjunglepark.com </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-102" title="Medieval Castle" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/medieval-castle.jpg" alt="Medieval Castle" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Medieval Castle</h3>\r\nFrom the moment you enter the grounds, you find yourself in an authentic medieval world. In theTournament Hall, the show of medieval fights and games will take place in the presence of the Counts in their Royal  Box seats. The Medieval adventure is an exciting and enjoyable attraction suitable for the whole family. It''s an experience that shouldn''t be missed! During the Tournament, you will be served the banquet just as it was done in medieval times; The soup is drunk and an entire chicken per person with its garnish  is eaten by hand. The dinner is completed with dessert and beverages.  Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.castillosanmiguel.com/castilloinformacion-en.html" target="_blank">www.castillosanmiguel.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-104" title="Yellow Submarine" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/yellow-submarine.jpg" alt="Yellow Submarine" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Yellow Submarine</h3>\r\nExperience a dive on board a real submarine which will take you below the waters of San Miguel Marina.You will experience the true underwater world of Tenerife. We offer a free daily bus service when you book your dive from the main resort areas of Tenerife (Playa de las Americas/ Los Cristianos/ Los Gigantes etc.).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.submarinesafaris.com/" target="_blank">www.submarinesafaris.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-105" title="Aqualand" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/aqualand.jpg" alt="Aqualand" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Aqualand</h3>\r\nAqualand is situated at San Eugenio (Alto) in the Costa Adeje region, and is the only water park in the South of Tenerife with a Dolphinarium.Its internationally awarded Dolphin Shows make this a complete leisure option guaranteeing the best in entertainment and enjoyment.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aqualand.es/tenerife/index.php" target="_blank">www.aqualand.es</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/quad-park.jpg" alt="Quad Bikes" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Quad Bikes</h3>\r\nExperience the thrill and challenge of negotiating cross country trails and circuits, whilst enjoying some of the best views in the south of Tenerife. There are 200,000 sq metres of trail riding routes and circuits for you to explore! Located just ten minutes from Los Cristianos / Las Americas. Free local collection from resorts available. Open from 9.30 a.m. until dusk, 7 days per week.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.quadparktenerife.com/" target="_blank">www.quadparktenerife.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/karting.jpg" alt="Karting" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Karting</h3>\r\nWelcome to the Karting Club Tenerife 1200 meters of fun and even 270 cc. of pure adrenaline! Come and experience the feelings of a professional behind the wheel! <strong>2 circuits:</strong> 1 senior and 1 junior to ensure maximum enjoyment for the whole family. The best facilities equipped with maximum security. Free bus service available.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.kartingtenerife.com/" target="_blank">www.kartingtenerife.com</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/la-gomera.jpg" alt="La gomera" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Island Tours &amp; Gomera</h3>\r\nThere are a wide variety of island tours in Tenerife taking in all the major natural attractions and locations. You may also like to book a full-day all- inclusive tour of the neighbouring island La Gomera. Trips may be booked thru any excursion agency in Tenerife.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/bob-diving.jpg" alt="Bob Diving" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Bob Diving</h3>\r\nFirst there was scuba diving... <strong>and then there was BOB Diving!</strong> All the underwater fun of traditional scuba diving, with much less effort. Despite looking like something secret agent 007 might use, you don''t need to be James Bond to enjoy exploring Tenerife''s underwater world. Our modern underwater scooters can be used by anyone. They are safe, easy and exciting. Safari BOB in Tenerife is the first BOB diving centre in Europe, operating since 1997, so while on holiday on the island, don''t miss the opportunity to enjoy a fabulous underwater experience that will be the highlight of your trip. You''ll find Safari BOB Diving in Puerto Colon, Playa de Las Americas, Pier no. 4.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.bob-diving.com/" target="_blank">www.bob-diving.com  </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top" width="200"><img style="width: 180px; height: 150px;" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/camel-park.jpg" alt="Camel Park" width="180" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td align="left" valign="top">\r\n<h3>Camel Park</h3>\r\nJust 10 minutes away from Los Cristianos and Playa de las Américas, in rural surroundings, you can have a nice time riding a camel, seeing the farm animals (goats, donkeys,ducks,hens,chicks,grey parrots or dogs) and enjoy an apertive drink at the typical canarian house of the place. In the farm there is a souvenir shop where you can purchase different presents and camel figures. There is free transport to the farm from the south of the island.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.camelpark.es/en/index.html" target="_blank">www.camelpark.es</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'Excursions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-19', '', '', '2012-03-27 14:17:36', '2012-03-27 14:17:36', '', 82, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/82-revision-19/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(513, 1, '2012-09-23 01:10:14', '2012-09-23 01:10:14', '<p><a href="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/monkey-park-1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-515" title="monkey-park-1" src="http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/wp-content/uploads/monkey-park-1-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>Described as the "biggest little zoo in the World", the Monkey Park Tenerife is an international breeding centre for endangered species of primates. Do not miss the chance on your holiday in Tenerife to visit The Monkey Park.</p>\r\n<p>It is situated in Arona off the TF1 motorway exit 26, less than 5 minute drive from the centres of both Los Cristianos and Playa de las Americas. It houses a great collection of monkeys, with many different species on display within the park.</p>\r\n<p>Where this zoo differs from others on Tenerife, and worldwide, is the fact that you can actually walk through the monkey cages and feed them and all the other animals you see in this zoo, and you will quickly see that each animal has its own favorite food. You honestly haven''t lived until you''ve had a Ring Tailed Lemur eating snacks from the palm of your hand. Sometimes some of the species get a lot bolder and will come and sit on your shoulder - especially the smaller monkeys, they have no qualms about jumping onto you and using their hands to reach into the bags of food.</p>', 'Monkey Park', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'monkey-park', '', '', '2012-09-23 14:58:33', '2012-09-23 14:58:33', '', 0, 'http://tenerife-apartments-online.com/tenerife/?post_type=location&#038;p=513', 0, 'location', '', 0),
